checked both at mint and at verify, strict re-verification of the parent
token at each hop (which catches parent-swap attacks that append-only
chains miss), and a dual enforcement model:

an operator ceiling plus per-parent narrowing. The workload identity
underneath is deliberately not redefined. The draft assumes a SPIFFE or
WIMSE credential and layers delegation on top.

